title: 141: Camus's "The Myth of Sisyphus"
dc:creator: A.J. Hanenburg
description: First, I get it, I hate the extra s after the apostrophe, but what're you gonna do, the MLA team are a bunch of nut jobs. That said, it doesn't matter anyway. We're all just doomed forever.
itunes:author: What does it matter? We're all doomed, so we're all the same.
itunes:subtitle: Whatever. It doesn't matter. It's (prepare for pun) revolting.
